3 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 151B IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) The Office of the Kentucky Center for Statistics shall produce a monthly
6 electronic report that shall:
7 (a) Include workforce need projections which are organized by industry, major
8 occupational group, geographic region, and necessary credentials or
9 training;
10 (b) Compare those workforce need projections with existing and projected
11 workforce availability as well as the availability of necessary credentials in
12 the Commonwealth;
13 (c) Highlight in-demand industries, occupational groups, and credentials by
14 geographic region; and
15 (d) Include a list of which in-demand jobs and credentials would leverage the
16 skills, experience, and credentials possessed by veterans.
17 (2) The office shall, at least once per month, forward this report, underlying data,
18 and any additional relevant information to:
19 (a) The Kentucky Commission on Military Affairs;
20 (b) Military outplacement offices;
21 (c) Vocational education centers; and
22 (d) Nonprofit programs which connect veterans to jobs.
