2 SECTION 7. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 164 IS CREATED TO
3 READ AS FOLLOWS:
4 The governing boards of all public institutions shall adopt rules and procedures to:
5 (1) Include veterans and National Guard members in any early course registration
6 period, if the institution offers an early course registration period to any segment
7 of the student population;
8 (2) Award full academic credit to a student who is called to active duty in the Armed
9 Forces of the United States for a course if at the time the student is called to
10 active duty:
11 (a) The student has completed at least eighty-five (85%) of the coursework
12 contributing to the final grade in the course, including but not limited to
13 exams and classroom attendance, if applicable; and
14 (b) Has a passing grade;
15 (3) Refund a portion of tuition and fees to a student who is called to active duty and
16 does not meet the requirements of subsection (2) of this section for academic
17 credit to be awarded, that portion being determined by taking the total amount of
18 tuition and fees paid by the student for the current academic term and
19 multiplying that total amount by the percentage of academic credits for which the
20 student is enrolled in the current term for which the student is not eligible to
21 receive academic credit under subsection (2) of this section; and
22 (4) Permit all veterans and any National Guard member who is returning from active
23 duty to do the following without incurring late fees or other penalties:
24 (a) File an application for admission at any time prior to the first day of classes
25 of the semester for which the applicant is seeking admission;
26 (b) Once an application has been filled but before the institution has issued a
27 determination on admission, register for available courses and permit the
