2 SECTION 11. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 40 IS CREATED TO
3 READ AS FOLLOWS:
4 The Kentucky Department of Veterans' Affairs shall create an initiative designed to
5 end veteran homelessness.
6 (1) As used in this section, "ending veteran homelessness" has the same meaning as
7 in the United States Interagency Council on Homelessness Criteria and
8 Benchmarks for Achieving the Goal of Ending Veteran Homelessness.
9 (2) The department shall develop and implement a strategy to meet the goal of ending
10 veteran homelessness within three (3) years of the effective date of this Act in
11 coordination with local, state, and federal government agencies and nonprofits,
12 and in consultation with states and cities that have achieved an end to veteran
13 homelessness in accordance with the criteria described in subsection (1) of this
14 section, including through:
15 (a) Coordinated community outreach and a common assessment tool;
16 (b) A community-wide, comprehensive list of veterans experiencing
17 homelessness, prioritized based on vulnerability;
18 (c) Data-sharing among all relevant providers, government agencies, and
19 Veterans Affairs Medical Centers;
20 (d) Increased coordination and streamlined processes for appropriate housing
21 placements;
22 (e) Connecting veterans experiencing homelessness to health, mental health,
23 employment, and training resources through the services described in this
24 section;
25 (f) A commitment to Housing First principles, as defined by the United States
26 Interagency Council on Homelessness; and
27 (g) Identification of and application for funding as needed.
